blocks.text: Defendants.
This matter having come before the Court on Motion for Default Judgment by Plaintiff,
CATALYST WEALTH ADVISORS LIMITED PARTNERSHIP III, an Arizona limited
partnership ("Plaintiff"). The Court, having reviewed the pleadings of record submitted by
Plaintiff in connection herewith, finds that Defendants, MARIA RITA LUPERCIO AVILA,
(MARIA) an unmarried woman and ANITA C. AVILA (ANITA) a married woman.
(collectively Maria and Anita shall be referred to as " Defendants") were served with the

Complaint and Summons by personal service on April 18, 2021 respectively, that Defendants had
actual knowledge of the matter, that Defendants failed to appear and answer Plaintiff's
Complaint within the period prescribed by law, that the default of Defendants is duly entered
by this Court. The Court finding that the sale of the 2016 tax lien certificate at auction for
Maricopa County APN 301-12-042 with an address of 9023 S. Calle Sahuaro, Guadalupe, AZ
85283, CP Number 16013700, to Plaintiff was valid, that Plaintiff complied with the
requirements of A.R.S. $ 42-18201 enotwijDomet, that the tax lien was redeemed by Defendants
14500 N. Northsight Blvd ., Suite 101
HYMSON GOLDSTEIN PANTILIAT & LOHR, PLLC
Telephone: 480-991-9077 / Facsimile: 480-443-8854
Scottsdale, Arizona 85260
after the commencement and service of this action, that Plaintiff is entitled to judgment
pursuant to A.R.S. $ 42-18206 for its attorneys' fees and costs, and there being no just reason
for the delay in the entry of this judgment, there being no further matters remain pending and
that this Judgment is being entered pursuant to Rule 54(c) of the Arizona Rules of Civil
Procedure. Based upon the foregoing findings, and good cause appearing therefore;
IT IS HEREBY ORDERED, ADJUDGED AND DECREED that Plaintiff be
awarded judgment against Defendants, MARIA RITA LUPERCIO AVILA and ANITA C.
AVILA, for its reasonable attorneys' fees in the amount of $1,940.00, and costs in the amount
of $1,070.23, for a total Judgment to Plaintiff and against Defendants of $3,010.23 with
interest at the legal rate of 4.25% per annum from the date of Judgment until paid.

Judge of the Maricopa County Superior Court
